        "id": 1,
        "name": "ReconnectED",
        "dateStart": "2025-01-26",
        "dateEnd": "2025-11-06",
        "visible": true,
        "status": "stable",
        "shortDescription": "Minimize the overconsumption of the internet. This project is one of the finalists for the EDUtech Asia 2025 - Planet Protectors Sustainability Challenge, which took place in Sands Expo & Convention Centre, Singapore. It placed as the 1st Runner-Up in the competition with a “Best Social Media Campaign” Peoples' Choice Award. It contains two components: a physical eco-planner and an AI-enabled Android companion app that helps users manage their screen time and encourages them to engage in offline activities.",
        "responsibilities": [
            "Secured 1st Runner-Up and “Best Social Media Campaign” award among 200+ international teams at the global EDUtech Asia 2025 - Planet Protectors Sustainability Challenge in Singapore.",
            "Engineered a full-stack Android application with Kotlin (Jetpack Compose), integrating Firebase Authentication and Firestore for secure user management and data.",
            "Built screen time tracking and limiting, Google Calendar integration, and an AI-powered assistant (Google Gemini API) to provide personalized support and reminders.",
            "Developed an interactive web dashboard using Nuxt.js (VueJS) for real-time visualization of screen time data."
        ],
        "links": [
